doc_summary_long: For the first time ever, 'no religion' has overtaken any single religious denomination, toppling Catholicism as the number one religious affiliation for Australians, the latest national census released on Tuesday revealed. In 1966 just 0.8% of Australians ticked the box for 'no religion', which includes atheist, secularists, and those who are agnostic. Those aged between 18 and 34 were most likely to report not having a religion (39%) than other age groups.
doc_summary_short: For the first time ever, 'no religion' has overtaken any single religious denomination, toppling Catholicism as the number one religious affiliation for Australians, the latest national census released on Tuesday revealed.
doc_title: 'No Religion' Is Now Australia's Number One Religion
